narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: My knowledge of Russian vastly increased over the short 5 weeks. I came in with a very limited skill set and now feel far more confident in my Russian.
I leaned to read, write, type, and speak Russian. The emphasis was on verbs of motion and aspect.
Professor Titus provided an in depth exploration of new grammar topics, and I feel as though I improved in that as well as in listening, speaking, reading, and writing.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Dr. Titus is incredibly caring and I appreciate how she is willing to work with her students to ensure that we succeed.
I think it is amazing. All strengths.
The class was amazing, only weakness is textbook answers are not provided online to check exercises.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would, but only if the student really wants to learn Russian. You have to be dedicated and willing to sacrifice free time.
I would absolutely recommend this course to other students!
